  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this activity is for students to use data presented in scaled bar graphs to solve one-step <q>how many more</q> and <q>how many fewer</q> problems. The graph in the previous activity was familiar to students since they had created it in the previous lesson, but the graph used in this activity is new to students. Because the graph has a scale of 10, students need to estimate values that do not show an exact multiple of 10. As a result, answers may vary slightly. Accept all answers that align to reasonable estimates.</p>
  </paragraphs>


